.TH LAN-CHAT 1 "May 2026" "lan-chat 1.0.4" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
lan-chat \- terminal based LAN chat application

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lan-chat

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lan-chat
is a decentralized terminal UI chat application for local networks.
Users connected to the same network can discover each other and send messages.

The interface is keyboard driven and built for terminal usage.

.SH CONTROLS

.TP
.B Tab
Toggle between UI components.

The currently focused component will have a purple colored border.

.TP
.B Up Arrow / Down Arrow
Navigate through the available users list.

.TP
.B Enter
Select the highlighted user.

When typing a message, press Enter to send the message to the selected user.

.SH HOW TO USE

.TP
1.
Start the application using:

.B lan-chat

.TP
2.
Wait for users on the same LAN network to appear.

.TP
3.
Use the
.B Tab
key to switch focus between components.

.TP
4.
Use the
.B Up Arrow
and
.B Down Arrow
keys to select a user.

.TP
5.
Press
.B Enter
to open the chat with the selected user.

.TP
6.
Type your message and press
.B Enter
to send it.

